{"name":"Zealot","type":"class","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/class.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bYUzZzY0eWDJFsVL"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<h1>ZEALOT</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Combining divine magic with martial skill, the Zealot is willing to follow through with extreme measures to enforce their deity&rsquo;s <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">will. Some Zealots stand side-by-side Champions on the field of battle while others become undercover agents bent on rooting out </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">corruption in their congregation. Others still infiltrate rival faiths and destroy them from the inside. But, regardless of their chosen </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">style, all Zealots are deeply dedicated to serving their deity, and all their foes will feel their righteous fervor.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>KEY ABILITY: </strong>STRENGTH OR DEXTERITY</p>\n<p>At 1st level, your class gives you an ability boost to your choice of Strength or Dexterity.</p>\n<p><strong>HIT POINTS:&nbsp;</strong>8 plus your Constitution modifier</p>\n<p>You increase your maximum number of HP by this number at&nbsp;1st level and every level thereafter.</p>\n<p><strong>SPELLS</strong></p>\n<p>Trained in divine spell attacks</p>\n<p>Trained in divine spell DCs</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>DURING COMBAT ENCOUNTERS</h2>\n<p>You channel divine magic into yourself to decimate your foes. Such is your faith that you may judge others for their affronts to your deity, filling you with righteous zeal.</p>\n<h2>DURING SOCIAL ENCOUNTERS</h2>\n<p>Your religious background makes you excellent at identifying scriptures and heretical works alike. But, depending on your training, you may also be the face of the party or the deceptive double-agent.</p>\n<h2>WHILE EXPLORING</h2>\n<p>Your training allows you to offer a diverse skill set, from detecting magical auras to sneaking in the shadows or standing in the front on guard for any signs of danger.</p>\n<h2>IN DOWNTIME</h2>\n<p>You frequently consult the scripture of your faith, determined to be a role model of your faith. You may also train with weaponry, especially those favored by your deity.</p>\n<h2>YOU MIGHT</h2>\n<p>● Consult with other followers of your faith to determine where you could best focus your efforts</p>\n<p>● Head a following of your own designed to teach the religious tenets of your deity</p>\n<p>● Become single-minded to the point of fault and be incapable of reaching a compromise with something you disagree with</p>\n<h2>OTHERS PROBABLY...</h2>\n<p>● Wonder how you became so zealous in your faith</p>\n<p>● Believe you can be strong-willed to the point of stubbornness.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Novel Options: Magic"},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.794,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2022-10-21T16:26:06.848-05:00","version":{"schema":0.769,"foundry":"10.288","system":"4.2.6"}}},"keyAbility":{"value":["dex","str"]},"items":{"snzv9":{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","name":"Deific Weapon","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-features.MvJQyWvzHyzt9CDt"},"57kwf":{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","name":"Deity","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-features.x2HOt3eP7MqCyCfo"},"t37cc":{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","name":"Divine Force","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-features.NofJAwnoFduDbqYR"},"708qo":{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","name":"Divine Spellcasting","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e-novel-options-magic.novel-magic-features.Zbr4hVxqnd59T5Ol"},"5wu62":{"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","name":"Inquisition","level":1,"uuid":"Compendium.pf2e